Channels allow group communication between users of the mud, and other muds
connected via intermud. Since working with others and communication is the
key benefit of an online system these functions are highly important.

The following are the key commands available:
The channel system can be accessed through the chan command:

chan        	Display a list of all channels available to you, and if you
		have them on or off.

Most of the channel commands take the form: chan (channel) /(action)
chan on gossip 		Join the gossip channel
chan off gossip 	Leave the gossip channel

To say something on the gossip channel you would use:
	chan gossip Hi how is everyone today?

emotes and/or socials
    ;   - You can use the semi-colon to send emotes in channel, best shown
          in example:

    >  chan gossip hi everyone
    [gossip] Mordain: Hi everyone
    >  chan gossip ;smile
    [gossip] Mordain smiles.

hist
    shows the channel history

    > chan hist gossip
    [gossip][Mar 18 19:54:14] Dil@Gev2: will have a laptop and mobile internet
    [gossip][Mar 18 19:54:54] Dil@Gev2: anyway, catch you later.
    [gossip][Mar 18 19:55:07] Han@Era: Have fun.

who
    if no arg, or the /who argument is given, chan will list who is
    subscribed to that channel.
    > chan who dgd

info
    Displays information about the specified channel.
    > chan info dgd

Access level: WIZ
new
    Access level: (WIZ)
    allows a new channel to be created

Access level: Admin
admin
    Toggle a channel as Admin only access Wiz and users will be denied

wiz
    Toggle a channel for Wiz access, player access will be denied

readonly
    Toggle a channel as readonly.
    > chan readonly dgdtest

permanent
    Toggle a channel as permanent.
    > chan permanent dgdtest

delete
    Removes the specified channel.
    > chan delete dgdtest

color
    sets the highlight color for all users

imud
    >  chan new dstest
    Channel created.
    >  chan imud dstest dead_test4
    >  chan on dstest
    Subscribed to dstest.
    >  dstest test
    >  [dstest] Admin@Warlords_Gurba: test

guild
   Toggle the channel to be for a specific guild.

   > chan guild fighters
   fighters is now a fighters guild only channel.
